                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                            <p>A carefully engraved wall inscription recording the donation after sale of a land in Kaṇṇamaṅkalam by eight Brahmins to the god Anantanārāyaṇa Paramasvāmi who graciously lies on the serpent bed (<foreign>aṇai</foreign>) at Tiruvekkā (Tiruveḵkā) in Kaccipēṭu (Kāñcipuram) for the sum of 367 <foreign>kaḻañcu</foreign>s of gold.</p>
                            <p>North wall of the central shrine.</p>
                        
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
                    <physDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <p></p>
                        </handDesc>
                    </physDesc>
                </msDesc>
